defaultany more
default and I 
defaultthink, if we consider where we are in the cycle of the industry, we are right at the beginning. The technology will improve within the heat pumps and performance will get better, as will knowledge among installers on how to utilise a heat pump. Used properly, I think there is no better technology with running cost savings against all fuels, including gas and obviously very big off-gas grid and lower carbon. So a busted technology I think is unfair and unfounded.
defaultDan defaultBylesdefault:default I thought that might be the case.
defaultChris Davidsondefault: Two points, one serious and one flippant, the serious point being that DECC’s data in the installed systems is extremely encouraging now and we get regular updates from DECC on fuel monitoring. Secondly, 
